        "title": "Our Beginnings",
        "content": "<p>Tufferman was founded in 2012 by Richard Gundle as a family-run business with a simple but clear objective: to challenge the overpriced and outdated model that had long dominated the shelving and racking industry.</p><p>Built on family values of honesty, fairness, and hard work, Tufferman was created to simplify the buying process and remove unnecessary mark-ups within the supply chain. From day one, the focus has been on delivering genuine value — high-quality shelving at sensible prices, backed by personal service you can rely on.</p><p>What began as a small family venture has grown into a trusted name across the UK. We have earned a strong reputation as a reliable and competitively priced supplier of high-quality storage solutions, including garage shelving, industrial shelving, workbenches, plastic storage boxes, and a wide range of storage systems for both commercial and domestic customers.</p><p>At Tufferman, we are proud to remain rooted in our family-business foundations — combining personal service with professional expertise.</p>",
